article.headline: Tennessee St. 62, Morehead St. 46
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Ladarious Weaver had 26 points off the bench to lead Tennessee State to a 62-46 win over Morehead State on Thursday night. Tennessee State (12-17, 8-11 Ohio Valley Conference) took a 33-22 first-half lead by shooting 47.8 percent from the field, including 7-of-15 3-point attempts. Morehead State (11-17, 7-12) struggled from the arc, shooting 3-of-16 and 32 percent from the field for the half. The Eagles were playing without senior Shaun Williams, who was suspended for the rest of the season on a violation of team rules. Weaver was 6-of-11 from 3-point range. Clarence Matthews added 12 points. Cordaryl Ballard led the Eagles with 14 points and Quentin Pryor had 12 points and a game-high eight rebounds. The Eagles controlled the boards 37-30.
